widgets_values: An image of the garment. This will be cropped to 3:4, then resized to 768x1024. Then we remove any background, and create a garment mask.
An image of the model. This will be dropped to 3:4, then resized to 768x1024. Then we remove the background.
Two images of the face to inpaint on the model. You can also use the same.
A description of the background to generate

This is where dress-up happens. After the initial run, you can come back here and check if the generated landmark coordinates look right. If not, you can update them manually and re-run the workflow for a better result.

We then remove the background to clear out any artefacts and prepare the image for background inpainting.
